	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator who was refused permission to fight as a gladiator in Caesar's games in 46 (Dio 43.23.5, reading #, rather than # with Boissevain). Syme suggests that he may have been confused with Furius Leptinus (62), a man of praetorian stock, who according to Suetonius (Iul. 39.1) did so fight. (RS, MSRP 1.281-282)[95x]\n" .
